                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Sacrificial Steel is additive with similar mods."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Steel",
                  "pageId": 1312691,
                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For example, a Galatine with a max rank Sacrificial Steel (full set bonus) and Maiming Strike will have a 10% × (1 + 275% + 150%) = 52.5% Critical Chance on Slide Attacks ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Steel",
                  "pageId": 1312691,
                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Sacrificial Steel is essentially the True Steel mod with Legendary rarity and 5 more ranks. It is considered the same mod as its Common counterpart, and thus both mods cannot be equipped together."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Steel",
                  "pageId": 1312691,
                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "The set bonus for Sacrificial Steel increases all stats given by the mod by 25% of mod's value per set pieces. At max rank with full set bonus, Sacrificial Steel grants a Critical Chance bonus of +275% and a Sentient damage bonus of +41.3% ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Steel",
                  "pageId": 1312691,
                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Sacrificial Steel is equal to True Steel at rank 5 when using 1 set piece. It outperforms at rank 4 when using 2 set pieces."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Steel",
                  "pageId": 1312691,
                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Umbra Mods have a unique Umbra polarity, whose matching polarity can currently only be found on Excalibur Umbra , Exalted Umbra Blade , and the Skiajati . It is possible to (re-)add an Umbra polarity to a mod slot but only through the use of Umbra Forma , which are unique rare rewards from Nightwave and Steel Path Honors , so it is advised not to re-Forma any mod slot with an Umbra polarity."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "pageTitle": "Sacrificial Steel",
                  "pageId": 1312691,
                  "revisionId": 2792487,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Similar to other faction damage mods (i.e. Smite Grineer ), the bonus damage against Sentients gets applied on top of the base damage and any added elemental damage of the equipped melee weapon (see Damage for complete mechanics)."
                }
              }
